Changing datatypes

data$TARGET <- as.factor(data$TARGET)

# Function to classify occupation types
classify_occupation <- function(occupation) {
  high_skilled <- c("Managers", "Accountants", "High skill tech staff", "Medicine staff", "IT staff")
  medium_skilled <- c("Sales staff", "Core staff", "Private service staff", "Drivers", "Cooking staff", 
                      "Secretaries", "Realty agents", "HR staff")
  low_skilled <- c("Laborers", "Security staff", "Cleaning staff", "Low-skill Laborers", "Waiters/barmen staff")
  
  # Classify occupation
  if (occupation %in% high_skilled) {
    return("High Skilled")
  } else if (occupation %in% medium_skilled) {
    return("Medium Skilled")
  } else if (occupation %in% low_skilled) {
    return("Low Skilled")
  } else {
    return("Unknown")
  }
}

# Apply the function to classify each occupation type in the data
data$Occupation_Type <- sapply(data$OCCUPATION_TYPE, classify_occupation)
quartiles <- quantile(data$AMT_INCOME_TOTAL, probs = c(0.25, 0.75), na.rm = TRUE)

# Define thresholds for skill levels
low_threshold <- quartiles[1]
high_threshold <- quartiles[2]

# Function to classify skill level based on AMT_INCOME_TOTAL
classify_Occupation_Type <- function(income) {
  if (income < low_threshold) {
    return("Low Skilled")
  } else if (income >= high_threshold) {
    return("High Skilled")
  } else {
    return("Medium Skilled")
  }
}

# Replace "Unknown" values in Occupation_Type with skill levels based on AMT_INCOME_TOTAL
data$Occupation_Type <- ifelse(data$Occupation_Type == "Unknown", 
                           sapply(data$AMT_INCOME_TOTAL, classify_Occupation_Type), 
                           data$Occupation_Type)
